<TEXT>
a former navy procurement official was 
sentenced to 15 months in prison friday for conspiring to help a 
connecticut contractor obtain a 100 million marine corps contract 
the defendant george w stone pleaded guilty in may to charges 
of copnspiracy and conversion of government property 
stone 46 formerly with the space and naval warfare systems 
command admitted passing confidential information about the 
contract for a communications system to a former boss mark c 
saunders then a consultant 
stone told saunders how norden systems inc was doing in the 
competition for the contract and saunders told the company 
he stood to gain nothing and in fact he gained nothing 
stones lawyer brian p getting told us district judge claude 
m hilton 
saunders is awaiting sentencing in the case 
stones case is one of more than 30 convictions resulting from 
the governments longrunning ill wind investigastion into 
defense contracts 
