<TEXT>
on some of the bolshoi ballets visits to the 
united states the evening of excerpts from ballets was the program 
to avoid not this year 
on friday night in a mixed bill at the new york state theater 
the bolshoi shone there was good dancing and a mix of dance styles 
plus variety in length of pieces presented 
the most applause went to nina ananiashvili and aleksei 
fadeyechev in the bravura grand pas from don quixote 
choreographed by alexander gorsky when he lifted her over his head 
with one hand the audience went wild yelena borisova also was 
excellent in her solo variation 
another spectacular pas de deux from marius petipas le 
corsaire was performed by alla mikhalchenko and mark peretokin 
his work in the air looked fantastic but his landings werent 
smooth 
the much softer pas de deux from the flower festival at 
genzano danced by natalia arkhipova and yuri klevtsov was 
programmed between the two flag wavers 
lyudmila semenyaka and yuri posokhov danced the fairy and the 
scot in a pas de deux from a bournonville masterpiece la 
sylphide 
yuri vasyuchenko starred in the appian way scene from 
spartacus choreographed by yuri grigorovich he and his 
shepherds and soldiers filled the stage with strong dancing and 
emphatic masculinity 
the evening began and ended with longer pieces in the opener 
mikhail fokines petrushka mikhail sharkov danced the title 
role showing a bit too much spunk as the pitiable puppet it ended 
with paquita choreographed by petipa to showcase several 
ballerinas the leading one in this performance nina semizorova 
doesnt make her movements flow but paquita to gentle music 
by leo minkus contained much beauty 
aleksandre kopylov conducted the new york city opera orchestra 
which has sounded marvelous through the twoweek engagement 
from here the company will perform in washington chicago los 
angeles san diego honolulu and boston 
</TEXT>
