to extend the ban on indecent broadcast material to 24 hours a day 
a court ruling on a 24hour ban is pending 
the fcc warned great american officials a year ago that material 
broadcast in 1987 on a show featuring disc jockeys bob kevoian and 
tom griswold on wfbqfm and its sister station wndeam may have 
violated the fccs indecency rules 
those rules prohibit the broadcast during daylight hours of 
language or material that depicts or describes in terms 
patently offensive as measured by contemporary community standards 
for the broadcast medium sexual or excretory activities or 
organs 
