<DOCNO> AP900721-0030 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
here is a brief profile of liberian rebel leader charles taylor 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
charles taylor 42 received a bachelors degree in economics 
from bentley college in waltham mass 
he returned to liberia from the united states where he worked 
as a factory mechanic after samuel doe took power in a 1980 
military coup 
doe named taylor head of the general services administration 
taylor fled to the united states in 1983 to escape charges of 
embezzlement 
he was arrested in the united states but escaped before he could 
be extradited 
taylors revolt began dec 24 1989 when he crossed the ivory 
coast border into liberia with a small band of men they accused 
doe of corruption mismanagement and human rights abuses taylor 
based his men in nimba county an area hostile to doe 
does foces responded with savage attacks on tribal groups that 
supported taylor international agencies say hundreds were killed 
and the atrocities appeared to have increased support for taylor 
as a civilian however taylor insists he is different from doe 
who made his career in the military he said he was leading a 
grassroots civilian uprising to get rid of a dictator but that 
he harbored no dictatorial ambitions himself 
</TEXT>
