important thornburgh said friday 
whitecollar criminals are less accustomed to hearing a jail 
door slam behind them than drug traffickers or violent criminals 
thornburgh told a law enforcement group that coordinates financial 
institution fraud investigations in the area 
a study completed by thornburghs office this week found that 
329 people have been indicted and 213 convicted 
we are seeking jail time in every case a major fraud has 
occurred thornburgh said were going to be busy in this area 
for the foreseeable future 
the savings and loan crisis should remain a high priority for at 
least the next five years because 530 thrifts remain under 
investigation he said 
thornburgh reiterated that there is no need for a special 
prosecutor to investigate president bushs son neil a former 
director of the failed silverado savings amp loan in denver 
im not aware of evidence of any allegations from a credible 
source that mr bush has committed any criminal wrongdoing he 
said 
earlier friday thornburgh criticized a major civil rights bill 
passed this week by the us senate the measure which is intended 
to protect women and minorities from job discrimination is opposed 
by the president 
the bill cannot be one that promotes the notion of quotas 
thornburgh said at an 8th circuit judicial conference workers 
