thermal insulation that was damaged during the launch of the soyuz 
tm9 capsule they must use to return to earth 
the strenuous space walk took two hours longer than planned and 
the cosmonauts could not reenter the spacecraft because of the 
sticky hatch soviet media reported 
their oxygen was running dangerously low and they were forced to 
use an emergency porthole on another part of the space station 
complex to get back inside seven hours after their exit 
once inside the cosmonauts apparently closed an inner hatch to 
seal one end of the airlock compartment that leads to the 
troublesome outside hatch 
