spain has maintained cordial ties throughout its own 
authoritarian and democratic administrations with the former colony 
both gen francisco franco and the democratically elected 
administrations that have governed spain since his death in 1975 
have assured castro easy credit to purchase spanish goods and 
finance longterm projects 
