the carrier uss abraham lincoln this year and has two other 
nimitzclass carriers under construction at newport news 
the washington built under the supervision of wb miff 
miffleton and james s morris is the third nimitzclass carrier to 
be assembled according to a modular plan involving 100tonormore 
sections called super lifts 
in the modular process super lifts are built in workshops 
and later lifted into place by crane to be welded together the 
process saved about 80 million and some 17 months in construction 
time 
the biggest piece is the 700ton bow section the deck house is 
seven decks high weighs 454 tons and lays atop the 4acre flight 
deck they were lowered into place by a 900ton crane that was 
built especially for carrier construction 
each of the nimitzclass carriers takes six years and 10000 
workers to complete before modular construction the ships were 
built one 40footby30foot panel at a time 
it was sort of like building a large house of cards 
miffleton said christening of the ship is the high point for the 
workers 
its like a fever that runs through the gang there may be as 
many as 2000 to 3000 workers on the ship at any one time they 
all feel they have a stake in her said morris veteran of 38 
years in the yard 
when the george washington is commissioned it will be home to 
2800 officers and men another 2700 will be aboard when the ship 
adds its air wing of 85 aircraft 
the carrier measures 1040 feet from bow to stern and 1092 feet 
on its flight deck from its keel to the top of its mast it is 244 
feet high the equivalent of a 24story building 
its top speed is about 45 mph 
