<TEXT>
the baltic republics on saturday quietly marked 
what lithuania called a day of injury humiliation and tragedy 
the 50th anniversary of the declaration of soviet power over them 
flags flew at halfstaff in the lithuanian capital of vilnius 
and latvia announced its lawmakers had voted to nullify the 1940 
declaration of soviet power 
for decades july 21 had been celebrated officially as a holiday 
in estonia latvia and lithuania but the three baltic republics in 
the last year have expanded their sovereignty and announced their 
intention to break with the soviet union 
lithuanias prime minister was quoted saturday as saying that 
negotiations with soviet officials on the republics march 11 
declaration of independence could start next week 
latvia lithuania and estonia were independent of moscow briefly 
between the two world wars but under a secret agreement stalin and 
hitler signed in 1939 they fell into the soviet sphere of 
influence 
soviet soldiers moved in as nazi forces attacked poland and 
under soviet pressure the parliaments of the three republics voted 
to join the soviet union 
they were admitted as soviet republics in early august of 1940 
thousands of lithuanians latvians and estonians were killed sent 
into exile or prison 
the latvian supreme soviet parliament voted thursday to void the 
50yearold declaration of soviet power aris yansons an assistant 
to latvian president anatoly gorbunov said saturday the 
proclamation strengthened the parliaments condemnation of the act 
in february 
the official soviet news agency tass quoted a latvian government 
statement saturday as saying july 21 1940 marked the start of 
mass terror and genocide against the residents of latvia the 
consequences of which are still being felt 
lithuanias government said in a statement saturday that the 
21st of july remains a day of injury humiliation and tragedy in 
our memory 
aidas palubinskas a spokesman for the lithuanian supreme 
council parliament said flags were flying at halfmast at the 
parliament building and a few other locations in vilnius 
