help support mrs maxwells three children in ohio 
it was wanda who bludgeoned a 73yearold fort myers woman to 
death during a squabble in 1979 over a ballpoint pen 
in that case a judge acquitted mrs maxwell of murder by reason 
of insanity and sent her to a state psychiatric hospital for 
treatment 
mrs maxwell was released in 1987 after state officials decided 
she was mentally competent 
