forest protection measure on californias november ballot 
in the second major event of redwood summer a series of 
protests against logging practices modeled after the freedom 
summer civil rights protests in the south demonstrators rallied 
for nearly two hours at a main intersection while police kept away 
a crowd of some 200 angry opponents 
some onlookers shouted go home and made obscene gestures 
the marchers shouted back we are home we are home 
