<TEXT>
herbert nelson a veteran actor whose 
credits include the guiding light soap opera and the television 
series maude has died at age 76 
nelson died of a stroke thursday at the actors fund of america 
nursing home in this new york city suburb 
a native of stillwater minn nelsons career began in the 
1930s with tent repertory and stock theater in the midwest 
he did more than 30 live radio shows in chicago including 
perry mason before moving to new york in 1940 when the 
guiding light radio show switched to television 
he was cast in his first broadway role in 1941 in sj 
perelmans the night before christmas and helped launch the 
nations first statesubsidized theater the barber theater in 
abingdon va nelson was also a founding member of the american 
federation of television and radio artists union 
the 1950s was marked by many roles in live television dramas and 
daytime serials including believe it or not the 
honeymooners perry mason and four years with hal holbrook in 
the brighter day 
he performed many times at the new york shakespeare festival 
under the direction of joseph papp including a role in 1964 as 
desdemonas father brabantio in othello 
while he worked in new york nelsons home was in suburban 
leonia where he was active in civic affairs he moved to venice 
calif in 1968 and lived there until 1989 
during the late 1960s and 1970s he had parts in many television 
shows including the bold ones the waltons little house 
on the prairie and maude 
his screen credits include little big man the great 
northfield minnesota raid the wilderness family and the 
hindenberg 
nelson is survived by two daughters two sons a brother and 
seven grandchildren 
services were scheduled for monday 
</TEXT>
